race.comment: SNEAKY SUNRISE (8) is a handy mare. It was a dash home in a rich mare's race at Flemington but she ran well. This looks a nice race for her with more tempo on. SOMEWHERE (9) was midfield first up but wasn't far away and come from a long way back. He'll relish a mile but he might concede a big start again. YES I KNOW (15) is lightly raced having worked home fairly fresh at Cranbourne on a day that favoured those on speed. He can improve off that. EXTREME VIRTUE (10) was solid fresh and will be fitter with each-way claims.
